    <title>The Humble Multiplication Table, 1</title>
    <content type='html'>&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiWospQYfSTFHNVanGTVlsjwxqL20WfSCbKExKLXxb_nWeh9sZkAbaSd5_aKgOMLzCZH9yNgFpDb_7gVK_slI_zIHsDFY_f8m93862cO0dH6pEISMyok64Tdik_Bdu7_yhTo34BaD5EDBk/s1600-h/385.JPG"&gt;&lt;img style="display:block; margin:0px auto 10px; text-align:center;cursor:pointer; cursor:hand;width: 400px; height: 157px;" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiWospQYfSTFHNVanGTVlsjwxqL20WfSCbKExKLXxb_nWeh9sZkAbaSd5_aKgOMLzCZH9yNgFpDb_7gVK_slI_zIHsDFY_f8m93862cO0dH6pEISMyok64Tdik_Bdu7_yhTo34BaD5EDBk/s400/385.JPG" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292102778520784882" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;A surprising relationship found in the multiplication table is that the sum of the entries in the main upwards diagonal and the diagonal above it is equal to the sum of the entries in the main downwards diagonal. What is also surprising is that this is but one among several observations about the multiplication table that can be expressed in terms of &lt;a href="http://mathrecreation.blogspot.com/2008/07/higher-polygonal-numbers-and-pascals.html"&gt;polygonal numbers&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This relationship involves three-dimensional triangular numbers (triangle-based pyramidal numbers, or tetrahedral numbers), and three-dimensional square numbers (square-based pyramidal numbers). Some values for these, and a few other polygonals, are shown below.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEia4iECXb2pguDxzsrt7oIGNPSvEbkVO3u0K5e2baE5KsRFyPQFqHndQkFLzEr-9JW3SNpaYHzA6JZDqTa6FfLNcPxs0oN-JTloKuT8brsnBQVnQhHMHQQnnPJ7Jho9POAlZzFwnYSsPiA/s1600-h/table.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEia4iECXb2pguDxzsrt7oIGNPSvEbkVO3u0K5e2baE5KsRFyPQFqHndQkFLzEr-9JW3SNpaYHzA6JZDqTa6FfLNcPxs0oN-JTloKuT8brsnBQVnQhHMHQQnnPJ7Jho9POAlZzFwnYSsPiA/s400/table.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292095963248981362" style="display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 291px; " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;To see why this relationship holds, first note that the sum of the entries in the &lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-style: italic;"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;th upward diagonal in the multiplication table is equal to the &lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-style: italic;"&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;th three-dimensional triangular number. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhHdxmiHGM559JGvZVdtPNEyNaTmH4zrz-rFtuh1m1hyC-i-ArFWE9bGYifg_mWoljfXvx73LI5uvNWJkcxGFWU0nJE6uUXlVjeF2cWh0AQ0pDbbLUg7UesnQgSAScB3rsYDzxzS-uVut8/s1600-h/eq_tetra.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEhHdxmiHGM559JGvZVdtPNEyNaTmH4zrz-rFtuh1m1hyC-i-ArFWE9bGYifg_mWoljfXvx73LI5uvNWJkcxGFWU0nJE6uUXlVjeF2cWh0AQ0pDbbLUg7UesnQgSAScB3rsYDzxzS-uVut8/s400/eq_tetra.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292095969850882434" style="display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 147px; " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Second, observe that he entries in the main down diagonal are square numbers (two-dimensional), so the sum of the main down diagonal is the &lt;span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-style: italic; "&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;th three-dimensional square number. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Finally, we use the fact that a square number (of any dimension) can be split into two triangular numbers (of the same dimension), which gives us the surprising result above.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiZOLd0DCt5kNHw2ZqVg90pHjNUg5ySFSsIj5i-xgSCJFcr9uctemb2b-ibmmP1pg-YICljW2tB7Nk4EejFhHn7jsGYzetR9GOkMlml9FL40d1sqKk5079ndUqQZjpDXbeet7-RIHFtACo/s1600-h/triangulation_eq.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEiZOLd0DCt5kNHw2ZqVg90pHjNUg5ySFSsIj5i-xgSCJFcr9uctemb2b-ibmmP1pg-YICljW2tB7Nk4EejFhHn7jsGYzetR9GOkMlml9FL40d1sqKk5079ndUqQZjpDXbeet7-RIHFtACo/s400/triangulation_eq.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292109047443935058" style="display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 175px; height: 57px; " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjMC8RzLE-D3lRHvinA3rXPHKPUp12vQAx5tMRCoirtObySeL4xFxI4uO8VTTof-gDOo2WWwqF8JW1TavK3DwFGhEmNKSEf8GXkb9sWWjh6iQ0ZTGJ8znJEj8XM9oPN0GlkJ6aXfvUG8LA/s1600-h/square-into-triangles.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEjMC8RzLE-D3lRHvinA3rXPHKPUp12vQAx5tMRCoirtObySeL4xFxI4uO8VTTof-gDOo2WWwqF8JW1TavK3DwFGhEmNKSEf8GXkb9sWWjh6iQ0ZTGJ8znJEj8XM9oPN0GlkJ6aXfvUG8LA/s200/square-into-triangles.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292102282577883122" style="display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 196px; height: 200px; " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The image below shows the relationship for a 4x4 multiplication table.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;a onblur="try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}" href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEihyphenhyphenvwGWC9vgVwsnQSb5oH67_UuAxZbaYqXuLLTFJvmBSe37JmNRTqXG2Zai2MTQWlCsZyYxwHYzAR5xmLzPc88sKZ0YLBH6Z_6dG4CNIbgY2IsMuCtFzn-bWWARNq-H2pU58ICr_hx9nM/s1600-h/4by4.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/b/R29vZ2xl/AVvXsEihyphenhyphenvwGWC9vgVwsnQSb5oH67_UuAxZbaYqXuLLTFJvmBSe37JmNRTqXG2Zai2MTQWlCsZyYxwHYzAR5xmLzPc88sKZ0YLBH6Z_6dG4CNIbgY2IsMuCtFzn-bWWARNq-H2pU58ICr_hx9nM/s400/4by4.jpg" border="0" alt="" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5292095971237577442" style="display: block; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 186px; " /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
